%% twinned and enantio
% COPY '#SCRIPT XHELP1'

The direct refinement of the Flack enantiopole (Flack(x) parameter
is a special case of twinning - twinning by inversion.

If you have a more general kind of twinning in a non-centrosymmetric
space group, then the twinning by inversion cannot be treated as a
special case, but must be handled via the twin matrices  - LIST 25

